IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: Serving over 20,000 guests each year, Michindoh Conference Center ministers spiritually, physically and emotionally to individuals, couples and families through a number of Michindoh sponsored programs designed to draw people into a closer relationship with Jesus Christ. Michindoh also serves the body of Christ through its retreat and conference center ministry, by providing a facility of excellence for God's people to conduct their Kingdom building programs and ministries.

IRS990.Description: Guest Groups: Accomodations and activities for retreats and meetings of other non-profit organizations. Michindoh provides a respsonsive Christ-centered enviroment of excellence by creating strategic opportunites for evangelism, nurturing, and training.

Activity2.Description: Outdoor Education: School children participate in an environmental program September through May. They are taught outdoor living skills, fire and shelter building, survival skills, teamwork, communication, and cooperative learning.

Activity3.Description: Program: Michindoh sponsered programs such as: summer and winter camps for children, couples retreats, and Family camps. Our focus is to provide wholesome fun, exprience the outdoors and most importantly how to know the Jesus Christ.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Michindoh files this 990 under the advisement of its governing body. This body will recieve a copy of the 990. Michindoh has also received assistance by its affiliation Spring Arbor University.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Charles Webb, board member of Michindoh and President of Spring Arbor University along with Damon Seacott, Board member of Michindoh and Vice President of Spring Arbor Univeristy would Hire and determine wage increases for the President of Michindoh Conference Center. All positions under the President can be filled and wages adjusted by the President of Michindoh. This became effective June 1, 2009

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The board of Michindoh Conference Center is in the process of creating a confilct of interest policy. The policy will include the process for disclosing the precise nature of interest if it falls in a "related individual or organization". There will be detailed description on how the conflict will be reviewed and resloved/disclosed. All board members will be required to sign a disclosure letter upon reading the policy.
